translated: Signe, former principal, Gothenburg, b. 22/10/80 in Stockholm to Henrik W. and Charlotta Eriksson. - Primary school teacher, graduated in 1902, graduated from teacher's seminar in 1913. Primary school teacher in Gothenburg from 1902-1917, regular subject teacher at Gothenburg practical intermediate school from 1917-1945, principal there from 1917-1924, part-time teacher at Gothenburg school kitchen seminar from 1914-1918, same at Gothenburg city elementary school seminar from 1916-1932, principal there from 1924-1932 (seminar closed). Member of Gothenburg general primary school board since 1923, as well as boards of various educational associations. Study trips to Norway, Denmark, Germany, Austria, Italy, and the USA. Married to Johannes, clergyman in Höreda, b. 25/2/93 in Rumskulla, Kalmar county, son of the minister A. P. W. and Matilda Sofia W. G. (married in 1893), with Stina Palemona, nee Lindgren. Children: Britta b. 1926, Anna-Stina b. 1928, Ulla b. 1929, Kerstin b. 1936. - Examination in Linköping, 1912, completed Bachelor of Arts in 1915, Bachelor of Theology, practical theology examination, and ordained as a priest in the Linköping diocese in 1921. Assistant curate in Norra Solberga, curate in Järeda in 1922, clergyman in Höreda in 1925.
